The "fade out" command, fo, is used to smoothly decrease the amplitude
at the end of the audio.  Type fo, a space, and the number of seconds
over which fading should be done.  The default is 1.0 seconds.  Fading is
linear when the fading time is more than two seconds, and it is S-shaped,
or an ogive, when less.  This command may be undone with the undo
command, u.

